Proof by Induction :-
let n = 2 ^ k,
base case k = 1, T(2) = 2*log 2^1 = 2 

Induction Hypothesis is the predicate T(k) = 2^k * log(2^k) = k*2^k

let T(2^(k-1)) be true, then,

T(2^(k-1)) = (k-1) * 2^(k-1)
T(2^k) = 2 * T ( 2 ^ (k-1) ) + 2^k

Substituting for T(2^(k-1)),

       = 2 * (k-1) * 2^(k-1) + 2^k
       = 2^k * (k-1+1) = k*2^k

Q.E.D.
